The page [here|http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/EHOSTING/Installing+Plugins] talks about how to install plugins for hosted products. 

It needs to be broken down into instructions for JIRA and Confluence, as Confluence plugins can be installed via the Plugin repository, while JIRA plugins require a support ticket to be created.

Thanks!

In http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Installing+JIRA+on+IBM+Websphere+6.x:
{quote}
When defining the datasource map it to the jdbc/JiraServerDS JNDI key. Please ensure that the JNDI key is set to jdbc/JiraServerDS and not jdbc/JiraDS.
{quote}

I suspected to be an extraneous step.

Can the requirement for this be found and listed next to the statement or the requirement be removed. The value of this task will remove uncertainty from the WAS61 JIRA integration documentation.

