This issue is raised so that we can track the task raised for Plugins: https://studio.atlassian.com/browse/PLUG-455

The problem affects instances of JIRA running on slow VMs or on machines under high load.

We should ideally have this fixed for 4.0.x but I guess that's up to scheduling.

The 'Clear Sorts' option in the Tools menu of the issue naviagator does not work. We basically do this:

{code:java}
final SearchRequest sr = getSearchRequest();
if (sr != null)
{
  // Lets just nuke the sorts so we will use the defaults
  sr.setQuery(new QueryImpl(sr.getQuery().getWhereClause(), new OrderByImpl(), sr.getQuery().getQueryString()));
}
return forceRedirect("IssueNavigator.jspa");
{code}

This means two things:

# We do remove the sorts from the filter in the session. However, 
# When we save the filter it actually saves the old JQL which means that we save the filter as it was before we removed the sorts.

This makes the action almost useless.

